page.title: 17WILDLIFE IN THE AREA
page.content: Talbot Woods is teeming with wild- life. It's important to have a woodland area because many people like to relax and walk through it or jog,walk their dog or just sit on a bench and admire the wildlife. Foxes live in the area, you can of- ten hear their cries at night. They also come into the town looking for food. Insect-eating bats also populate the woods, you'd see them at night search- ing for moths and mosquitoes. Mice live here, field mice and dor- mice are most common. Field mice are largely nocturnal, they are prey of tawny owls and barn owls. Confined to the woods by day, they emerge to- wards dusk in search of voles, field mice,moles and other small animals.
